export const ART_RECIPE_VERSION = 'v34';  // BRIDGE DECKS CARRY THE ROAD. A bridge composed as a bare structural slab: the `deck` part emitted its masonry (or timber) deck box and two parapets, and nothing else ŌĆö no running surface. That is only half a bridge, and it read as exactly half: the terrain's painted road ribbon deliberately STOPS at the banks (over the span the ground beneath the deck is the carved channel BED ŌĆö metres below, under the water plane ŌĆö so painting cobble there would smear road colour down the channel walls), which leaves the deck as the ONLY place the road can cross. With no roadway on it, the road simply ended at the river and a blank stone slab crossed the water. The `deck` part gains a `roadway` param (a `RoadState.surfaceMaterial`: dirt|gravel|cobble|paved) and lays it as a thin (0.12 m) surface course on the deck top, inset between the parapets ŌĆö dirt/gravel as earth (gravel coursed random_rubble), cobble as stone with `cobble` sett work, paved as stone ashlar flagging. `buildBridgeObject` resolves it through the caller's `roadSurfaceFor(edgeId)`, which worldgen wires to `edgeRoadProfile(...).state.surfaceMaterial` ŌĆö THE same value the painted ribbon derives its pavedness from ŌĆö so the cobble that arrives at the bank is the cobble that crosses. Unset ŌćÆ a bare deck, byte-identical (the `roadway` param is `any`, so it injects no default). Every composed bridge sprite changes ŌćÆ version bump + a vendored-bundle reseed; the golden fixtures (cottage, stone box ŌĆö no deck) hold. (v33 ŌĆö ALPINE FLORA FIDELITY (compose half): (1) BARE-CROWN VARIANT AXIS ŌĆö `branch_plant` gains a `bare` param (blueprint/parts/flora-branch.ts): the same skeleton composed with its LEAVES DROPPED and terminal limbs extended ~22% (fine winter twigs, not a pruned stump). ParametricPlantSource exposes it as variant slot `FLORA_BARE_VARIANT` (= FLORA_VARIANTS = 3), composed lazily like variants 1ŌĆō2 from the VARIANT-0 skeleton (seed 0); the draw list